The European Union is changing the rules for the issuance of a visa
The people must go to the centres of Service for Non-refundable claimants Visa before their interview in the Consular Section; the cost the waiting time will be reduced.
As of 10 January 2011 the processing of visas at the Embassy and consulates of the United States will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will have to submit to the Service for Non-refundable claimants Visa (CSA, according to its acronyms in English) before their interview in the Consular Section.
The staff of CSA will take biometric information from the applicant, which will be reviewed by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will present some advantages for candidates, among which is the following:
The total cost to deal with the visa will be lower, it will no longer be necessary to make a payment to get an appointment, another payment for the treatment of visa and another for mail service delivers the document.
The aspiring will make a one-time payment to cover the three services.
The current tariff will remain the same: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 in the case of visas with application (ci-inclut visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for visas of traders and investors.
The people who want to renew their visas will not have to go to an interview with the Consular Representative, they arise only to the CSA closer to where they will submit the documents and we will take their fingerprints.
Due to the fact that biometric information will be made in the CSA, applicants who want a second appointment to be interviewed in the Consular Section stay less time than before.
Similarly, visa applicants to the Consulates in Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the extra fare of $26.
